<br>
1. You receive one point per two hours of raiding<br>
<br>
2. If you arrange a raid  you receive one extra point.<br>
<br>
3. If you behave inappropiate in a guild raid, you will receive a warning, if you have received two warnings in the same raid you will lose a point, if you receive three or more warnings, you may be asked to leave raid.<br>
<br>
4. Loot will be bid for in increements of two points, if a member have below two points and is the only wishing a piece of loot, the member will be allowed to loot, but will receive no points for the raid. A member with less then 2 points may not bid on an item, but only give tell that she/he is interested.<br>
<br>
5. Bidding for loot is CAWU (Can And Will Use) you are not allowed to bid for items just to twink an alt or sell it for money in the first round. If no Chars on the raid want the item, it is open for bidding to alts/sell/whatever.<br>
<br>
6. With the coming of Planes of Power, it is now possible to turn in old Hate and Fear armor for a minute XP reward and a gem. Therefor in future Hate / Fear raids all armor that no one can't or won't use will be auctioned to members for the minimum of 1 point (exception to rule 4). <br>
<br>
7. NO DROP items will be taking care of as soon as possible, while dropable items will be looted by whoever is lootresponsible at the raid. When there is a break in the raid, or at the raid end, the loot will be distributed as discussed above. Dropable loot that no one wants goes to the scarab bank to be sold for cash to fund scarab raids.<br>
All cash loot and vendor sold items goes to the lootresponsible after a raid.<br>
<br>
8. Invited persons to a guild raid will only be allowed to loot something if no present guild members can't or won't use it. On a rare occasion an outsider will be invited because we could not do a raid without that person (or class). In that case she may be allowed to roll on a choosen item with others on raid that wants the item (example: pandemic got a chance to roll on chanter epic).<br>
<br>
9. All expenses for a scarab raid will be refunded to the person who have expenses. (Peridots, Pearls, Gatestones, Coffins) Raid Leader is responsible for keeping score of eventual debt to a scarab member.<br>
<br>
(10. If a raid is hosted as an open raid/invited raid, regular rules dont apply , instead all drops is randomed between whoever is interested or the raiding guilds rules are used. <br>
If 40% of the raid force is members of scarab (and not members of the guild hosting the raid) points will be awarded after scarab rules.) &lt;--- currently under discussion.<br>
<br>
11. The raid leader can &quot;change&quot; or &quot;not follow&quot; all the rules, if he got the support of a big majority of the raid force.<br>
However permanent changes must be discussed on the scarab board.<br>
<br>
This is ruthlessy stolen from the guild discussion about RP system (a bit changed and added tho) Thanks Wildroot. (our raid officer)<br>
I think this could work better then our current system as it allows for most alternatives. it is not as simple theoretically as the point whipe system, but it is simpler in the practical sense and easier to follow.<br>
This does however require either the ML or all the members to know their point status, so that is up to us to keep it up to date.<br>
